<h2>FAQs About Ghirardelli White Chocolate Chips and Gluten</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>1. Are Ghirardelli white chocolate chips safe for people with celiac disease?</h3>
    <p>Ghirardelli white chocolate chips are considered gluten-free by the company, but they are not certified gluten-free. They are produced in facilities that handle wheat, which may pose a risk of cross-contamination. Individuals with celiac disease should exercise caution and consider certified gluten-free alternatives.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>2. Does Ghirardelli provide a list of gluten-free products?</h3>
    <p>Yes, Ghirardelli provides a list of gluten-free products on their official website. Their white chocolate chips are included in this list, but they are not certified gluten-free.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>3. What are some certified gluten-free white chocolate chip brands?</h3>
    <p>Brands like Enjoy Life offer certified gluten-free white chocolate chips. These products are tested and verified by third-party organizations, making them a safer choice for individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivity.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>Ghirardelli white chocolate chips are a popular choice for bakers, and the company considers them to be gluten-free. However, the absence of gluten-free certification and the potential for cross-contamination in their manufacturing facilities mean that they may not be entirely safe for individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivity. For those who need to avoid gluten at all costs, it may be wise to opt for certified gluten-free alternatives. Always read labels carefully and consult with a healthcare professional if you have any doubts about a product's gluten content.</p>

